For those that don't know - Ernie Coombs, aka Mr. Dressup, was something like Mr. Rogers &amp; Capt. Kangaroo.  American by birth, he took citizenship 30 years after he started his show, but was a staple program for, well, pretty much my entire life.<br>
<br>
His show often featured promising talent.  &quot;Allyson&quot; went on to do &quot;The Big Comfy Couch&quot; as 'Lunette' and now hosts the CBC morning kids shows.  Many well-known Canadian musicians and performers made appearances as well.<br>
<br>
